{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Layout","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Animatable","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animatable","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10AnimatableP"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You traditionally arrange views in your app’s user interface using built-in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layout containers like "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"Grid","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". If you need more complex"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layout behavior, you can define a custom layout container by creating a type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that conforms to the "},{"code":"Layout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol and implementing its required"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"methods:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/sizeThatFits(proposal:subviews:cache:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reports the size of the composite layout view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/placeSubviews(in:proposal:subviews:cache:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"assigns positions to the container’s subviews."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can define a basic layout type with only these two methods:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct BasicVStack: Layout {","    func sizeThatFits(","        proposal: ProposedViewSize,","        subviews: Subviews,","        cache: inout ()","    ) -> CGSize {","        \/\/ Calculate and return the size of the layout container.","    }","","    func placeSubviews(","        in bounds: CGRect,","        proposal: ProposedViewSize,","        subviews: Subviews,","        cache: inout ()","    ) {","        \/\/ Tell each subview where to appear.","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use your layout the same way you use a built-in layout"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container, by providing a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewBuilder","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" with the list of subviews"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to arrange:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["BasicVStack {","    Text(\"A Subview\")","    Text(\"Another Subview\")","}"]},{"anchor":"Support-additional-behaviors","type":"heading","text":"Support additional behaviors","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can optionally implement other protocol methods and properties to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"provide more layout container features:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Define explicit horizontal and vertical layout guides for the container by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementing ","type":"text"},{"code":"explicitAlignment(of:in:proposal:subviews:cache:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for each dimension.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Establish the preferred spacing around the container by implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/spacing(subviews:cache:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Indicate the axis of orientation for a container that has characteristics"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a stack by implementing the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"layoutProperties-5rb5b"},{"type":"text","text":" static property."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create and manage a cache to store computed values across different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layout protocol calls by implementing "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/makeCache(subviews:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The protocol provides default implementations for these symbols","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if you don’t implement them. See each method or property for details.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Add-input-parameters","type":"heading","text":"Add input parameters","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can define parameters as inputs to the layout, like you might","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct BasicVStack: Layout {","    var alignment: HorizontalAlignment","","    \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the parameters at the point where you instantiate the layout:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["BasicVStack(alignment: .leading) {","    \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the layout provides default values for its parameters, you can omit the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parameters at the call site, but you might need to keep the parentheses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after the name of the layout, depending on how you specify the defaults.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, suppose you set a default alignment for the basic stack in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the parameter declaration:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct BasicVStack: Layout {","    var alignment: HorizontalAlignment = .center","","    \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To instantiate this layout using the default center alignment, you don’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have to specify the alignment value, but you do need to add empty","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parentheses:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["BasicVStack() {","    \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Swift compiler requires the parentheses in this case because of how the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"layout protocol implements this call site syntax. Specifically, the layout’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/callAsFunction(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":" method looks for an initializer with exactly zero","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"input arguments when you omit the parentheses from the call site.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can enable the simpler call site for a layout that doesn’t have an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implicit initializer of this type by explicitly defining one:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["init() {","    self.alignment = .center","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For information about Swift initializers, see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/LanguageGuide\/Initialization.html","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Swift Programming Language"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Interact-with-subviews-through-their-proxies","type":"heading","text":"Interact with subviews through their proxies","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To perform layout, you need information about all of its subviews, which","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are the views that your container arranges. While your layout can’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interact directly with its subviews, it can access a set of subview proxies","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/Subviews","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" collection that each protocol method receives as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an input parameter. That type is an alias for the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutSubviews","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"collection type, which in turn contains ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutSubview","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" instances","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that are the subview proxies.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can get information about each subview from its proxy, like its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dimensions and spacing preferences. This enables","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you to measure subviews before you commit to placing them. You also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"assign a position to each subview by calling its proxy’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutSubview\/place(at:anchor:proposal:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" method.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Call the method on each subview from within your implementation of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"layout’s ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/placeSubviews(in:proposal:subviews:cache:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Access-layout-values","type":"heading","text":"Access layout values","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Views have layout values that you set with view modifiers.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Layout containers can choose to condition their behavior accordingly.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, a built-in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" allocates space to its subviews based","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in part on the priorities that you set with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/layoutPriority(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view modifier. Your layout container accesses this value for a subview by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reading the proxy’s ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutSubview\/priority","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" property.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can also create custom layout values by creating a layout key.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Set a value on a view with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/layoutValue(key:value:)","isActive":true},{"text":" view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier. Read the corresponding value from the subview’s proxy using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"key as an index on the subview. For more information about creating,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"setting, and accessing custom layout values, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutValueKey","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Associated-Types","generated":true,"title":"Associated Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/Cache"]},{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/callAsFunction(_:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/explicitAlignment(of:in:proposal:subviews:cache:)-5ucm5","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/explicitAlignment(of:in:proposal:subviews:cache:)-9jxaf","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/makeCache(subviews:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/placeSubviews(in:proposal:subviews:cache:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/sizeThatFits(proposal:subviews:cache:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/spacing(subviews:cache:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/updateCache(_:subviews:)"]},{"anchor":"Type-